Description: Fragment of a mud stopper that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The back is slightly concave and shows impressions of organics in smaller depressions but is very eroded in general. The upper side is slightly convex and shows parts of a larger seal impression covering an area of 4.0 x 2.5 cm. Recognisable is a seated figure with long hear, the head itself is not preserved, the figure is facing towards the left, underneath an n and underneath a pr-sign (O1).
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
